{"id": 1139, "title": "Ticket #1139: Master doesn't invalidate its ad on shutdown", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen the master shuts down, it doesn't invalidate its ad in the collector.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2010-Jul-01 10:39:27 by psilord:</em> <br/>\n\nHow does this relate to <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"abandoned\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=53\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('53'); return false;\" title=\"condor_master's invalidate attempt delays shutdown\">#53</a></span>?\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2010-Jul-27 16:58:32 by slauson:</em> <br/>\n\nI got the master to invalidate its ad using CollectorEngine::invalidateAds(), but I think that using CollectorEngine::remove() would be better in a large pool. After looking around, it looks like the Startd is the only daemon to actually use this method. I will try to see if I can do something similar for the master.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body><blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"../files/204/patch.diff\">patch.diff</a>\n1952 bytes added by slauson on 2010-Jul-29 19:29:00 UTC.\n</li></ul>\n</blockquote></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Aug-10 09:57</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=18754\">[18754]</a></span>: Fix double free in master introduced in <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=1139\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1139'); return false;\" title=\"Master doesn't invalidate its ad on shutdown\">#1139</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2010-Jul-29 16:56</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"